We could get fancy and use streams in place of that `for` loop. Not necessarily better in this case, but more fun. 

We are going to call `Stream::count`. This returns a long, so change our use of 32-bit integer to 64-bit long. Or else you could cast the long to an integer.

Calling [`List::stream`][4] generates a stream of the `Person` objects held in the list.

A [`Predicate`][5] object holds our test for gender and our test for maturity. The call to [`Stream::filter`][6] applies the predicate to select objects. These get counted by a call to [`Stream::count`][7]. 

